08/07/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Representatives of the BiH Federation and Republika Srpska met in Sarajevo on Monday (7 July) to discuss joint steps for setting up a single market and unified economic policies. 
Organisers pushed for establishment of a unified customs policy, tax system and mechanisms promoting local production.
Also Monday, the World Bank resident office in Sarajevo signed two loan agreements with BiH, worth a total of $7m. 
The Social Insurance Technical Assistance Project will receive $5.2m, and the remaining $1.8m will support initiatives for development and protection of forests. 
(SRNA, Onasa - 07/07/03)
